        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 8 at 1:28PM CDT until May 8 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>SVRMEG

The National Weather Service in Memphis has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Weakley County in west Tennessee...
West central Henry County in west Tennessee...

* Until 215 PM CDT.

* At 127 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Dresden, or 7
miles southeast of Martin, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Matheny Grove, Ralston, Ore Springs, Dresden, Cottage Grove,
Palmersville, Como, and Martin.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
